---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Image License | Designed by Anthony"
  description="Licensing terms for images, logos, and visual assets used on designedbyanthony.com."
  hideBreadcrumbs={true}
>
  <section class="license-page">
    <div class="license-container">
      <h1>Image Licensing</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 1, 2026</p>

      <div class="license-section">
        <h2>At a glance</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Image licensing</strong> is how we document who may use photos, illustrations, and brand
          assets that appear on this site. Logo and custom work stay with Designed by Anthony; many editorial
          photos follow the Unsplash License.
        </p>
        <ul class="license-tldr">
          <li>Brand marks require written permission before reuse.</li>
          <li>Most blog photography is Unsplash-licensed (see below).</li>
          <li>Some covers are commissioned or generated and are site-only.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For the rest of the site, start from the <a href="/">homepage</a>, browse the <a href="/blog">blog</a>, or
          see <a href="/services">services</a> and <a href="/portfolio">portfolio</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="license-section">
        <h2>Site Logo and Brand Assets</h2>
        <p>
          The Designed by Anthony logo, wordmark, and all brand identity assets displayed on this
          website are the exclusive property of Designed by Anthony and are protected under
          applicable intellectual property laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          These assets may <strong>not</strong> be reproduced, distributed, modified, or used in
          any commercial or non-commercial context without prior written permission from Designed by
          Anthony. To request permission, please use the{' '}
          <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="license-section">
        <h2>Photography and Editorial Images</h2>
        <p>
          Photographic images used on blog posts and other editorial pages are sourced from{' '}
          <a href="https://unsplash.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Unsplash<span class="sr-only">(opens in new window)</span></a>{' '}
          and are licensed under the{' '}
          <a
            href="https://unsplash.com/license"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Unsplash License<span class="sr-only">(opens in new window)</span>
          </a>
          . Under this license, images may be used freely for commercial and non-commercial purposes
          without attribution, though attribution is appreciated.
        </p>
        <p>
          To acquire a license for any specific Unsplash image used on this site, please visit{' '}
          <a href="https://unsplash.com/license" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            unsplash.com/license<span class="sr-only">(opens in new window)</span>
          </a>
          .
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="license-section">
        <h2>Custom-Commissioned Images</h2>
        <p>
          All custom illustrations, screenshots, diagrams, and other bespoke visual content created
          for this website are the property of Designed by Anthony unless otherwise credited. All
          rights reserved.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some blog cover images (for example <code>/images/upstate_local_seo_cover.png</code>) are
          generated or commissioned artwork used only on this site and are not covered by the
          Unsplash License above.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="license-section">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For licensing inquiries, permission requests, or questions about a specific image, contact
          us through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. For general policies, see the{' '}
          <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>, <a href="/terms">terms of service</a>, and{' '}
          <a href="/cookie">cookie policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .license-page {
    padding: clamp(7rem, 10vw, 8.25rem) var(--container-gutter) var(--section-space);
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .license-container {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text-cream);
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .license-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .license-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-white);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-gray);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: #93c5fd;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text-white);
  }

  .license-tldr {
    color: var(--text-gray);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.35rem;
  }

  .license-tldr li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }
</style>
